page.title: 05Banstead Wood Ground Flora
page.content: A rich, mixed and prolific ground flora typifies the varied aspect, drainage and pH in the wood. A 30 minute July stroll was used to make this list. It is not exhaustive: Dog's Mercury{Sanicle}Nettle{Figwort Rat-Tail Plantain{Wood Dock}Timothy Willowherb{Wood Spurge}Cocksfoot Bugle{Heath Speedwell}Yorkshire Fog{ Wood Avens{Wood Sedge}Spearthistle Goosegrass{Thyme-leaved Speedwell Perforate St'John's Wort; Cuckoo Pint Bluebell{Yellow Pimpernel}Smoothrush Bracken{Pendulous Sedge}Ground Ivy Woody-Nightshade{Deadly Nightshade} Burdock{Great Mullein (2m. tall)} Forget-Me-Not{Comfrey}Wild Strawberry Silverweed; White Deadnettle Tormentil; Yellow Archangel; Selfheal Red Campion{Broad-Leaved Buckler Fern {Enchanter's Nightshade}Male Fern Woody plants surveyed on another page.
